I had him as a PI for the PCL472 project course; he's amazing! He is very knowledgeable, kind, and helpful. He always replies to emails promptly and even helped me write my thesis, down to the very details. Very approachable, and his lectures are easy to understand and listen to!
Great prof - funny, you learn interesting material, he wants you to do well and his assessments are very fair with no trick questions.

Definitely my favourite class of undergrad. Although I did not have a very strong background in the material presented, it was extremely interesting. He is very passionate about what he teaches and definitely ignited my interest in academia and research.

One of the best profs around. He's Emeritus but still teaches. Trained as a psychologist (trained hypnotist) he integrates many fascinating fields in PCL475: pharmacology is only half the course, the rest is psychology and neuroscience masterfully entwined into fantastic lectures and debates about various disorders and the treatments available.
